---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base
  title="AI Project Standard"
  description="A starting baseline for open-source projects that use AI. Four pillars: human-AI collaboration, open-source operations, software engineering, knowledge and documentation."
>
  <section class="flex flex-col gap-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
      A starting baseline for open-source projects that use AI.
    </h1>
    <p class="max-w-2xl text-lg">
      Four pillars, three profiles, five adoption paths. Clone the template, browse the playbook.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href={`${base}use-cases`}
        class="rounded-md bg-[var(--color-accent)] px-5 py-2.5 font-medium text-white no-underline hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)]"
      >
        See the use cases
      </a>
      <a
        href={`${base}profiles`}
        class="rounded-md border border-black/15 px-5 py-2.5 font-medium no-underline hover:bg-black/5 dark:border-white/15 dark:hover:bg-white/5"
      >
        Compare profiles
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Four pillars</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Human-AI collaboration</h3>
        <p>
          <code>AGENTS.md</code> as the source of truth, multi-tool pointer files for Claude Code,
          Codex, GitHub Copilot, and Cursor, and the operational <code>.ai/</code> workspace.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Open-source operations</h3>
        <p>
          README, LICENSE, contribution rules, security policy, support guide, issue and PR templates,
          code owners, funding, citation.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Software engineering</h3>
        <p>
          CI workflows, versioning policy, Git workflow, branch protection, dependency automation,
          security baseline, OpenSSF Scorecard.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Knowledge and documentation</h3>
        <p>
          The strict in-repo <code>docs/</code> reader and this knowledge layer — long-form guides,
          comparisons, blog, research.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Three profiles</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-lg border border-black/10 p-6 dark:border-white/10">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Open Source</h3>
        <p>Governance, contribution, security, CI. No AI files.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-lg border border-black/10 p-6 dark:border-white/10">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Human-AI Collaboration</h3>
        <p>
          <code>AGENTS.md</code>, multi-tool pointers, <code>.ai/</code> workspace. Drops into an
          existing repository.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-lg border border-black/10 p-6 dark:border-white/10">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Combined</h3>
        <p>All four pillars. The full reference implementation in this repository.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Five adoption paths</h2>
    <ol class="ml-5 list-decimal space-y-2">
      <li>Greenfield AI-native project — Combined profile, day one.</li>
      <li>AI into an existing repository — Human-AI Collaboration profile alongside what already exists.</li>
      <li>Clean open-source start — Open Source profile only.</li>
      <li>Professionalising an existing open-source project — pull in the parts that are missing.</li>
      <li>AI and open source from scratch — Combined profile, full stack.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Walk-throughs for each path live in <a href={`${base}use-cases`}>Use cases</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-20 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Two-layer architecture</h2>
    <p class="max-w-3xl">
      The repository is the operational layer — workflows, AI state, governance, templates. This site
      is the knowledge layer — explanations, comparisons, tutorials, research. The repository itself
      serves as the reference implementation: every file and workflow runs here, not just on paper.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
